name: Pocket Planets | Mercury | #001
description:
Star System: Solar System
Number of Moons: 0

Mass: 3.301 × 10^23 kg
Radius: 2440 km
Surface Gravity: 3.7 m/s^2
Orbital Period: 88d
Length of Day: 58d 15h 30m

Description: Mercury is the smallest planet in the Solar System and the closest to the Sun. The planet is in synchronous rotation with the Sun with the surface temperature reaching 700K in the day and dropping to 100K at night. Mercury is too small and hot for its gravity to retain an atmosphere making the planet a dead, silent planet.
